  * Full-time fixed term position for 6 months 
  * Access to flexible working arrangements including hybrid working options 
  * Based at our vibrant [ St Lucia ](https://campuses.uq.edu.au/st-lucia) campus 

##  ** About UQ **

As part of the UQ community, you'll have the opportunity to work alongside the
brightest minds, who have joined us from all over the world.  
  
Everyone here has a role to play. As a member of our professional staff
cohort, you will be actively involved in working towards our vision of a
better world. By supporting the academic endeavour across teaching, research,
and the student life, you'll have the opportunity to contribute to activities
that have a lasting impact on our community.  
  
Join a community where excellence is at the core of our culture, contributions
are valued and a range of [ benefits and rewards
](https://careers.uq.edu.au/why-work-at-uq) are available, such as:

  * 26 weeks paid parental leave or 14 weeks paid primary caregiver leave 
  * 17% superannuation contributions 
  * 17.5% annual leave loading 
  * Health and wellness discounts - fitness passport access, free yearly flu vaccinations, discounted health insurance, and access to our Employee Assistance Program for staff and their immediate family 
  * On campus childcare options 
  * Cheap parking (from just $5.75 a day) 
  * Salary packaging options 

##  ** About This Opportunity **

The ** Senior Application Technical Analyst ** undertake solution design,
development, implementation, testing and documentation of solutions across ERP
systems at the University of Queensland.  
  
Key responsibilities will include:

  * Champion and enforce robust cybersecurity practices in alignment with UQ's Cyber Security Policy and procedures. 
  * Undertake solution design, implementation, testing and documentation of solutions to deliver features that meet customer requirements while managing stakeholder expectations around system and resource constraints. 
  * Collaborate with key stakeholders to analyse business processes, identifying operational needs and proposing innovative solutions for automated and non-automated components, fostering process improvements. 
  * Take responsibility for the creation of test cases and test scripts using in-depth technical analysis of both functional and non-functional specifications. Conduct and facilitate testing activities in accordance with the approved Test Strategy. 
  * Lead project management for significant IT projects, engaging in negotiation and liaison with senior stakeholders to ensure adherence to organisational policies and strategies. Provide senior technical advice, support, and mentoring while maintaining an in-depth knowledge of business processes and systems. 
  * Provide senior technical advice, support and mentoring to other team members, acting as an escalation point for complex issues and facilitating the resolution in line with service delivery expectations. Maintain an in-depth knowledge of business processes and systems sufficient to provide expert advice on their application. 

This is a 6-month ** full-time, fixed-term ** position.  
  
At HEW level 8, the full-time equivalent base salary will be in the range
$108,975 - $122,176, plus a generous super allowance of up to 17%. The total
FTE package will be up to $127,500- $142,946 annually. As this role is covered
by an Enterprise Agreement, you will also receive regular remuneration
increases - at least once a year.

##  ** About You **

You'll be a highly driven individual with previous experience delivering and
enhancing projects and initiatives within the SDLC environment. In addition,
you will possess:

  * Postgraduate qualifications in IT, business, or a related field, or demonstrate significant progress towards such qualifications, coupled with extensive relevant experience. An equivalent combination of experience and education/training will also be considered. 
  * Significant experience in business analysis and requirements gathering, technical solution design, testing, correcting and documenting solutions within a large ERP system. 
  * Experience in solution design and risk management activities to ensure the robustness of proposed solutions, with the demonstrated ability to collaborate with stakeholders, including vendors and other technical teams, to manage these to resolution. 
  * Strong communication and interpersonal skills, including the demonstrated ability to effectively mentor and provide technical leadership to other team members and to communicate and negotiate effectively with a diverse range of stakeholders to achieve outcomes. 
  * Excellent written communication skills, including the demonstrated ability to write clear and precise user and technical specifications, with the ability to prioritise own workload, work independently and meet deadlines. 
  * Strong technical knowledge and experience in designing, testing, coding, and documenting complex programs and scripts for Oracle PeopleSoft applications is desirable. 

In addition, the following mandatory requirements apply:

  * ** Work Rights: ** You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this appointment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment. 
  * ** Background Checks: ** All final applicants for this position may be asked to consent to a criminal record check. Please note that people with criminal records are not automatically barred from applying for this position. Each application will be considered on its merits. 

